         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">3/6/93. ¶ In my letter of yesterday ¶  I forgot to mention, that the larger plant, taken in the “Australian” for Kew by Mr and Mrs Markes may possibly not be a Verticordia, but perhaps a Melaleuca; th...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">93.06.03a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew. Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1891-1896. f. 48.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Correspondent inferred from contents and context of other letters; see M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 7 March 1983.</p>
               </note>3/6/93.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Date stamped</seg> Royal Gardens Kew 10. Jul. 93.; <seg style="font-style: italic; ">annotated in red ink by W. Hemsley</seg>:<seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>ackd 18.VII. 93 (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">letter not found</seg>). </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">In my letter of yesterday<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">The latest know letter to Thiselton-Dyer preceding this one was dated 31 May 1893, and is not concerned with the matters discussed in the present letter.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I forgot to mention, that the larger plant, taken in the “Australian” for Kew by Mr and Mrs Markes may possibly not be a Verticordia, but perhaps a Melaleuca; the smaller however must be either V. oculata or V. grandis; this smaller one however is in so feeble a state, that it may perish on the way.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Annotated beneath the postscript</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">by William Watson</seg>:<seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>Only <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
                     </seg> plant has been recd. at Kew. It arrived quite dead. / W.W. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">The left margin of the annotation is marked by a double line in red pencil.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Like in some other myrtaceous plants, the oildots in the leaves of the larger plant are <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">few</hi>
               </seg>; still they are there and comparatively large and often only developed near the upper end of the leaves. But supposed, the large plant prove not a true Verticordia, when coming into flower, it will turn out likely <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">new for Kew</hi>
               </seg>. I trust, you will have a friendly word for Mr &amp; Mrs Markes.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With best greeting</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I had just a very touching letter from Casimir D.C.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The letter doubtless concerned the death of de Candolle’s father, Alphonse de Candolle, who died on 4 April 1893. M gave a memorial address at the meeting of the Field Naturalists’ Club of Victoria on 8 May 1893 (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Victorian Naturalist</seg>, vol. 10, p. 18); see B93.06.04, reprinted B93.10.01.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Melaleuca%20">Melaleuca </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Verticordia%20oculata">Verticordia oculata</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Verticordia%20grandis">Verticordia grandis</name>
            </p>
         </div>
